race.comment: SUBTERRAIN (7) hit the frame here on debut before getting the job done at Ipswich last time out. Looks like the runner in this field with the most upside and rates among the leading chances. LITTLE JEANIE (1) has hit the top-five at her past seven starts and only needs some luck navigating from the sticky alley to be playing a major role in the outcome. SAN GABRIEL (2) looked good saluting at Doomben at the latest effort and Moor stays on top. Will prove tough to hold out again. NINJITZOU (4) has been thereabouts in recent efforts and may earn some minor money again. LIETUVA (10) best of the rest.
